"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-03-20-thierry-henry-sends-message-kylian-mbappe-real-madrid-move-olympics-call-20497726\", \"text\": \"Thierry Henryfully expectsKylian Mbappeto sign forReal Madridand will continue pushing for the forward's inclusion in his Olympic squad thissummer.  The France captain is thought to have agreed a move to the Santiago Bernabeuwhen his contract at Paris Saint-Germain expires in June.  A move to the Spanish capital will see Mbappe link up with fellow France internationals Eduardo Camavinga, Aur\\u00e9lien Tchouam\\u00e9ni and Ferland Mendy who will all hope to be involved in France's Euro 2024 squad this summer.  The three are also selection options for Les Blues at Paris 2024, with Arsenal legend Henry leading the side as they seek to win gold on home soil.  Clubs across Europe are bracing themselves for selection rows however with the campaign in Paris set to clash with the start of new domestic seasons in August.  Real Madrid have already sought to lay down a marker, with L'Equipe reporting Real Madrid will refuse to release any of their players.  Arsenal could find themselves in a similar position with William Saliba, who could be picked for the squad.  Metro's Head of Sport James Goldman delivers punchy analysis, transfer talk and his take on the week's biggest stories direct to your inbox every week.  Sign up here, it's an open goal.  Henry however will keep pushing to ensure every player his available.  'I have not spoken to Kylian about it yet,' Henry said in an interview with Le Parisien.  'But, what do you want me to say to him and what do you want Kylian to say to me? Is he going to fight with his club? Be careful, here we are speculating without knowing if his destiny will be his.  'The only thing we know about Kylian is that he is leaving. It does not matter where he goes. But if he goes to Real Madrid, we already know that they will not let their players go.  Henry continued: 'I would not stop there. We are talking about Kylian, but there are also Camavinga, Tchouam\\u00e9ni and Mendy. I will keep trying until the end, because I want the best team.  'But we return to the same debate: What can be done apart from being polite, asking and asking again and again?  'It's like when, at Christmas, you have asked your parents for the same gift ten times, without result, and you ask for it again for the eleventh time\\u2026 You have to ask for it. Who stops at the first refusal?'  ArrowMORE:England backed to win Euro 2024 with 'the best bunch of young players' by Sir Geoff Hurst  ArrowMORE:Young Arsenal star reveals club blocked him from leaving on loan in January  ArrowMORE:Arsenal star Ben White is a 'great character' and 'deserves' to play for England, says Conor Coady  Sign up and tell us which team you support to get personalised updates about your club.  Select your team for football news tailored to youClose  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"